{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d19e4e17-576a-4bfc-9108-197925f39b8a","content":"For a .NET Web API with authentication, use the `webapi` template:\n\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth <option>\n```\n\n**Authentication options (`--auth`):**\n\n| Option | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Azure AD for a single tenant |\n| `MultiOrg` | Azure AD for multiple tenants |\n| `Windows` | Windows authentication |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```bash\n# Single-org Azure AD\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --domain yourdomain.onmicrosoft.com --tenant-id <id> --client-id <id>\n\n# Azure AD B2C\ndotnet new webapi --auth IndividualB2C --domain yourdomain.b2clogin.com\n\n# Minimal API with OpenAPI (no auth, add manually)\ndotnet new webapi --use-minimal-apis\n```\n\nFor JWT bearer auth without Azure AD, start with `--auth None` and add `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer` manually.\n\nRun `dotnet new webapi --help` to see all available options for your SDK version.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"483d6244-349c-4a78-9147-824757357854","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This seems like a general .NET development question. Let me check if there's relevant content in the repository that might help answer this, particularly in the plugins directory.\n\nActually, looking at the context, this is a general question about creating a web API project with authentication. This is likely about .NET/ASP.NET Core templates. I can answer this from general knowledge without needing to search the repository, but let me check if there's relevant documentation in the repo first.\n\nActually, I should just answer this from my knowledge since it's a straightforward question about dotnet templates and authentication options. No need to search the codebase for this.","outputToken